# ğŸ“Œ **What Is Wiâ€‘Fi Lab Controller?**

Wiâ€‘Fi Lab Controller is an **educational GUI toolkit** that allows you to experiment with Wiâ€‘Fi functions **safely on your own equipment**.

It is made for:

* Raspberry Pi
* Parrot OS
* Kali Linux
* Ubuntu (with wireless tools installed)
* Any Linux system with **aircrackâ€‘ng**, **hostapd**, **dnsmasq**, and **NetworkManager**

â— **This tool is strictly for lab experiments on your own Wiâ€‘Fi network.**

It does **NOT** include any malicious intent â€” all functions require manual confirmation and can be restored with the *End Attack / Restore Normal* button.

---

# ğŸ“¥ **Installation**

Install required dependencies:

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install python3 python3-tk aircrack-ng hostapd dnsmasq network-manager xdg-utils
```

Clone your repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/ZahidServers/WiFi-Lab-Controller.git
cd Wifi-Lab-Controller
cd wifilab
```

Run:

```bash
sudo python3 app.py
```

(root or sudo required)

## ğŸ“¥ Installation (Linux / Parrot / Kali / Debian / Ubuntu / Raspberry Pi OS) via PyiPi

### ğŸ”§ Required System Packages

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y python3 python3-tk aircrack-ng hostapd dnsmasq network-manager xdg-utils
```

